<h2 class="wp-block-heading">What is Pneumonia?</h2>



<p>Pneumonia is an infection in the lungs that causes breathing to become difficult. It occurs when the small air sacs in the lungs, which are also called alveoli, become filled with either fluid or pus. This can lead to a cough with mucus, fever, chills, chest pains, and breathing problems.</p>



<p>It can be bacterial, viral, or fungal and is not necessarily something severe, but still quite severe at times. Some of the people who are usually vulnerable are children, older people, and anyone with a weak immune system. Pneumonia starts like the flu but can last longer and become serious if not treated early. </p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Symptoms of Pneumonia</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Persistent <a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/how-homeopathy-can-help-in-treating-cough"   title="Cough" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked"  data-wpil-monitor-id="2101">Cough</a>:</strong> Sometimes clears liquids, such as mucus or phlegm, which can vary in color to yellow or green or contain blood.</li>



<li><strong>Fever and Chills:</strong> Fever is often said to be high, and the patient may sweat and have chills.</li>



<li><strong>Shortness of Breath:</strong> Shortness of breath or having a feeling that you are trying to breathe through a narrow straw even when you are lying down.</li>



<li><strong>Chest Pain:</strong> Pain localized or concentrated, aching, sharp, or stabbing that becomes worse with deeper breaths and coughing.</li>



<li><strong>Fatigue: </strong>Exhaustion and physical exhaustion – factors that prevent one from performing the usual work.</li>



<li><strong>Rapid Breathing and Heart Rate:</strong> Shallow or rapid breaths or pulse because of low oxygen levels.</li>



<li><strong>Blue Lips or Fingertips:</strong> Namely due to oxygen deficiency in some instances.</li>



<li><strong><a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/how-to-treat-loss-of-appetite-with-homeopathy"   title="Loss of Appetite" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked"  data-wpil-monitor-id="2476">Loss of Appetite</a>:</strong> Loss of appetite and/or thirst because of disease.</li>



<li><strong>Confusion:</strong> Especially in older patients, there can be complaints of confusion or disorientation.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Causes of Pneumonia</h2>



<p>Pneumonia is caused by infections that lead to inflammation in the lungs. The main causes include:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Bacteria: </strong>Usually results from bacteria known as Streptococcus pneumoniae. Bacterial pneumonia can develop from a <a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/how-to-treat-cold-with-homeopathy"   title="cold" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked"  data-wpil-monitor-id="2434">cold</a>, flu, or other conditions or caused by a general compromise of the immune system.</li>



<li><strong>Viruses: </strong>Causes include viruses such as flu, RSV, and coronaviruses such as COVID-19 affected age groups include children.</li>



<li><strong>Fungi:</strong> Conditions caused by Histoplasma or Coccidioides are typical of fungal infections in patients with immunosuppression.</li>



<li><strong>Aspiration:</strong> Pneumonia resulting from breathing in food, liquid, or vomit into the lungs may occur.</li>



<li><strong>Hospital-acquired Pneumonia:</strong> Acquired during a hospital or other healthcare facility stay, most often due to drug-resistant organisms.</li>



<li><strong>Community-acquired Pneumonia:</strong> Contracted in environments other than healthcare facilities; often through exposure to people with the virus.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Does Homeopathy for Pneumonia Work?</h3>



<p>Homeopathy can complement conventional medicine in treating pneumonia. It aims to help individuals regain health by matching remedies to their specific symptoms, providing comfort for cough, fever, and chest pains. Common homeopathic remedies include Bryonia for dry cough, Phosphorus for breathing issues, and Antimonium Tart for thick, yellow mucus.</p>



<p>Homeopathy is safe and has no side effects, focusing on the patient&#8217;s overall well-being. However, pneumonia can be serious, so homeopathic treatment should only begin after consulting a qualified homeopath alongside traditional medical care.</p>



