<li><strong>Phosphorus:</strong> Ideal for people with wheezing and chest tightness and those with blood-stained or rust-colored sputum. For those who do not feel well and have a desire for cold beverages, it is ideal.</li>



<li><strong>Antimonium Tart:</strong> Good for treating profiles such as the production of excessive mucus, products cough, and difficulty breathing. Most beneficial for older adults or those who have weak muscles in their respiratory systems.</li>



<li><strong>Hepar Sulph:</strong> Used for treating a cough manifested with thick, greenish mucus production and intolerance to cold drafts. This is preferable for anyone with chills and sudden stabbing chest pain.</li>



<li><strong>Kali Carb:</strong> Desirable in case of severe chest pain, shortness of breath, and a chronic cough. It can be used when there is an aggravation of the symptoms at the break of dawn.</li>
