<li><strong>Frequent Small Meals:</strong> One should take several small meals per day to avoid overloading their stomach. These include toast foods and boiled potatoes and also conditions such as crackers.</li>



<li><strong>Avoid Dairy Products: </strong>In the early stage of typhoid, one should not take milk since it is likely to cause complications like diarrhea or bloating.</li>



<li><strong>Protein-Rich Foods:</strong> When the fever is down, try to introduce foods containing lean proteins, such as boiled chicken, eggs, lentils, and the rest.</li>



<li><strong>Fruits and Vegetables:</strong> Raw and crispy vegetables and fruits, including bananas, apples, and papayas, ease digestion and provide vitamin and mineral needs.</li>
</ul>



