					<description><![CDATA[<p>What is Melasma? Melasma is a chronic skin disorder in which the skin becomes brown or grayish brown on the facial area. This process happens when the skin is overproducing melanin, the substance that gives skin color. This is more common in females, especially pregnant females (known as the mask of pregnancy) or females who use contraceptive pills. Melasma usually begins in adult women and can be aggravated by the sun, hormones, or some medications. Affected regions are normally the forehead, cheek area, nose as well as upper lip. Melasma is not damaging in any form but causes discomfort for </p>
<p>The post <a href="https://weclinic.in/blog/how-to-treat-melasma-with-homeopathy">How To Treat Melasma With Homeopathy?</a> appeared first on <a href="https://weclinic.in/blog">WeClinic&trade; Blog</a>.</p>
