<li><strong>Monitor Hormonal Changes</strong>: Some women should be cautious about hormonal changes associated with their menstrual cycle or pregnancy, which can make melasma worse.</li>



<li><strong>Avoid Smoking and Alcohol</strong>: Avoid smoking and drinking moderately because both these habits are bad for your skin and worsen any pigmentation concerns.</li>
